# Cloudflare Pages configuration
#
# ── _redirects ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Single Page App — every URL that doesn't match a static file or a route
# folder we pre-render must fall through to the SPA shell. Pre-rendered
# route folders (dist/<route>/index.html) take precedence because they're
# matched first as static files; this block is the safety net for any
# new route that hasn't been pre-rendered yet (e.g. /blog/<new-slug>).
#
# We also redirect the legacy /signup path to /auth?next=/signup so old
# links still work, and the /billing path that the docs mention to the
# real /dashboard page (where the top-up button actually lives).

# 301 redirects first (they match before the SPA fallback)
/signup   /auth?next=/signup   301
/billing  /dashboard            301
/blog/:slug.md  /blog/:slug    301

# SPA fallback: anything that didn't match a static file → index.html.
/*    /index.html   200
